%section.tbs-section
  %h1.page-header#input-groups Input Groups
  %p.lead
    Extend form controls by adding text or buttons before, after,
    or on both sides of any text-based input.
    Use
    %code .input-group
    with an
    %code .input-group-addon
    to prepend or append elements to a single
    %code .form-control

  %h2#input-groups-buttons Button addons
  %p
    Buttons in input groups are a bit different
    and require one extra level of nesting.
    Instead of
    %code .input-group-addon
    you'll need to use
    %code .input-group-btn
    to wrap the buttons.
    This is required due to default browser styles
    that cannot be overridden.

  .tbs-example
    .input-group
      %input.form-control
      %span.input-group-btn
        %button.btn.btn-default
          = icon 'search', '', class: 'fa-lg'
  .highlight
    :markdown
          .input-group
            %input.form-control
            %span.input-group-btn
              %button.btn.btn-default
                = icon 'search', '', class: 'fa-lg'
